# Praxion Per-Project Rules Configuration
#
# Disables Praxion rules for this project. The SessionStart hook reads
# this file and applies the disable list through two mechanisms — together
# they give the YAML uniform reach across every Praxion rule:
#
#   - `install: hook-deliver` rules → filtered out of the SessionStart
#     `additionalContext` payload (rule body not delivered to the session).
#   - `install: symlink` rules → reconciled into `claudeMdExcludes` in
#     `.claude/settings.json` as portable globs of shape
#     `**/.claude/rules/<id>.md`. Claude Code's runtime then skips those
#     rule files even when a matching `Read` would otherwise trigger them.
#
# Defense-in-depth: the `claudeMdExcludes` mechanism also covers
# `install: hook-deliver` rules in the disable set, so a stale symlink
# left in `~/.claude/rules/` by a prior install (e.g., when a rule's
# install type flipped from `symlink` to `hook-deliver`) cannot bypass
# the blacklist. The structural prune happens in the installer's
# `sweep_stale_rule_symlinks` step; this is the runtime safety net.
#
# Core rules (`core: true`) are non-disableable; attempting to disable
# one emits a SessionStart warning and the rule remains loaded.
# Organization-managed-policy rules deployed at platform locations are
# also immune to this mechanism (a Claude Code platform constraint).
#
# The hook is idempotent. It recomputes the derived `claudeMdExcludes`
# entries on every SessionStart, replacing only Praxion-managed entries
# (those whose pattern starts with `**/.claude/rules/`) and preserving any
# other entries you added to `.claude/settings.json` by hand. Removing an
# entry from this YAML triggers a clean removal of the corresponding
# `claudeMdExcludes` entry on the next SessionStart.
#
# === Token-savings ceiling ===
# The maximum baseline token reduction is the sum of the *hook-deliver*
# rule sizes — currently ~5,100 tokens across three rules (memory-protocol,
# agent-model-routing, vcs/git-conventions). Path-scoped rules cost zero
# tokens at SessionStart; disabling them yields a *policy guarantee* but
# no baseline savings. Core rules are non-disableable. To shrink the
# always-loaded surface further, the lever is the `core: true/false`
# classification in `rules/_manifest.yaml`, not the YAML disable list.
#
# === Behavior contract ===
# Fail-open everywhere — the hook never blocks SessionStart:
#   - File missing → all rules load (backward-compatible default).
#   - Malformed YAML → stderr warning + all rules load.
#   - Schema `version: > 1` → stderr warning + all rules load.
#   - `disable:` provided as a scalar (e.g. `disable: ml/*` without `- `)
#     → stderr warning + treated as empty.
#   - A pattern in `disable:` matching zero rules → stderr warning per
#     pattern (typo guard).
#   - Duplicate entries in `disable:` are harmless (fnmatch results are
#     deduplicated via a set internally).
#
# === Kill switch ===
# Set `PRAXION_DISABLE_RULE_INJECTION=1` to disable injection entirely
# for one session — useful for debugging rule interactions without
# uninstalling. Hook-deliver bodies are suppressed; previously-written
# `claudeMdExcludes` entries remain in effect via Claude Code's runtime.
#
# Full enumeration of disableable rules — what `disable:` can actually target.
# Canonical source: `rules/_manifest.yaml`. Full token accounting and rationale:
# `docs/rules-taxonomy.md`. Five core rules are NON-disableable (CLAUDE,
# swe/adr-conventions, swe/agent-behavioral-contract,
# swe/agent-intermediate-documents, swe/swe-agent-coordination-protocol) —
# attempting to list them emits a SessionStart warning and they stay loaded.
#
#   Hook-deliver, always-loaded (3 rules — disabling reclaims SessionStart tokens):
#     - swe/memory-protocol            — Memory MCP protocol (~1.2k tokens)
#     - swe/agent-model-routing        — Per-agent Claude model tier policy (~1.6k tokens)
#     - swe/vcs/git-conventions        — Commit/staging/secrets conventions (~1.0k tokens)
#
#   Path-scoped (13 rules — zero baseline cost; disabling is a declarative
#   guarantee that the rule never applies here, even if a trigger file appears):
#
#     SWE (6 rules):
#       - swe/coding-style                — Language coding conventions (.py/.ts/.go/.rs/etc.)
#       - swe/id-citation-discipline      — REQ/AC citation discipline in source code
#       - swe/shipped-artifact-isolation  — Artifact-portability constraint (rules/skills/etc.)
#       - swe/staleness-policy            — Skill freshness conventions (skills/**/SKILL.md)
#       - swe/testing-conventions         — Test code patterns and discipline
#       - swe/vcs/pr-conventions          — PR workflow and merge policy
#
#     ML/AI (3 rules):
#       - ml/eval-driven-verification        — Training plan acceptance criteria
#       - ml/experiment-tracking-conventions — Experiment tracking tool conventions
#       - ml/gpu-budget-conventions          — GPU compute budget enforcement
#
#     Writing (4 rules):
#       - writing/aac-dac-conventions     — Architecture-as-Code fence conventions
#       - writing/diagram-conventions     — Diagram toolchain (Mermaid, LikeC4, D2)
#       - writing/html-output-conventions — HTML dashboard output rules
#       - writing/readme-style            — README writing style
#
#   Glob shortcuts (fnmatch; `*` crosses `/`):
#     - ml/*       → all 3 ML rules
#     - writing/*  → all 4 writing rules
#     - swe/vcs/*  → swe/vcs/git-conventions + swe/vcs/pr-conventions
#     - swe/*      → 9 SWE rules (3 hook-deliver + 6 path-scoped); core rules
#                    emit a warning and stay loaded

# List of rules to disable for this project, by ID (directory-prefixed
# path without the `.md` extension). fnmatch glob syntax is supported.
disable:
  # Project sets PRAXION_DISABLE_MEMORY_MCP=1 or has no memory MCP server
  # - swe/memory-protocol

  # Not an ML project — never load ML training conventions, even if a file
  # like `prepare.py` or `runs/` appears in the tree for unrelated reasons
  # - ml/*

  # Project uses default model routing only (no multi-tier pipeline)
  # - swe/agent-model-routing

# Schema version. Currently 1. Bumped on breaking config changes.
version: 1
